"Oh, never, never may he suffer through me!" was her soul's most fervent prayer;
                  "let sorrow, danger, death come, if God will, but let our hearts still be one.
                  Welcome any thing, everything but estrangement from him!"

Again she sang,— 



"Other refuge have I none;

Hangs my helpless soul on thee;

Leave, oh! leave me not alone

Still support and comfort me.

All my trust in thee is staid,—

All my help from thee I bring;

Cover my defenceless head

With the shadow of thy wing."

"All is safe!" cried Moreland, as they threw themselves into his arms, clinging to
                  him in an agony of emotion—"all is well! Look up, my Eula! Sister, be not afraid;
                  it is all over! Here is Paul, who is ready to die in my defence. "
